Ι would just observe, in this place, that, in the course of my essay, no labour of mine has aimed at the support of any one preeonceived hypothesis. My opinion is not what I brought with me, to the reseamh, but what has been the result of inquiries. It was gradually formed, and was impressed, by the force of evidence. I aim at no conceit of invention. My utmost pretension is, to re-discover what has been long concealed, by collecting facts, which, for many centuries, have been preserved in an insulated state. In every period and stage of the disquisition, Ihave adduced what appears to me competent evidence.
